The design of the Bluetooth Arcade Controller shield for the Arduino is contained in this directory. The hardware was designed with the free and open source CAD tool called KiCad, available from http://kicad.sourceforge.net/wiki/index.php/Main_Page. The KiCad files for the circuit schematic, circuit board layout, and part libraries are contained in the kicad/ directory. The rendered production-ready gerber files are contained in the gerbers/ directory.
